  "term": "def:bernstein-polynomial",
  "kind": "Definition",
  "title": "Bernstein Polynomial",
  "root": "",
  "statement": "Let $n \\in \\mathbb{N}$ and let $f:[0,1]\\to\\mathbb{R}$.\nA function $B_n:[0,1]\\to\\mathbb{R}$ is called the $n$th Bernstein polynomial of $f$\nif and only if, for every $x \\in [0,1]$,\n\\[\nB_n(x)=\\sum_{k=0}^{n} f\\!\\left(\\frac{k}{n}\\right)\\binom{n}{k}x^k(1-x)^{n-k}.\n\\]",
